%global packname  CARS
%global packver   0.2.2
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.2.2
Release:          3%{?dist}%{?buildtag}
Summary:          Covariate Assisted Ranking and Screening for Large-ScaleTwo-Sample Inference

License:          MIT + file LICENSE
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel >= 3.2.2
Requires:         R-core >= 3.2.2
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-np 
BuildRequires:    R-stats 
Requires:         R-CRAN-np 
Requires:         R-stats 

%description
It implements the CARS procedure, which is a two-sample multiple testing
procedure that utilizes an additional auxiliary variable to capture the
sparsity information, hence improving power. The CARS procedure is shown
to be asymptotically valid and optimal for FDR control. For more
information, please see the website
<http://www-bcf.usc.edu/~wenguans/Papers/CARS.html> and the accompanying
paper.

